SIMPLE: safe
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Safe
<hw>Safe</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Safer</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Safest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>sauf</ets>, F.
<ets>sauf</ets>, fr. L. <ets>salvus</ets>, akin to <ets>salus</ets>
health, welfare, safety. Cf. <er>Salute</er>, <er>Salvation</er>,
<er>Sage</er> a plant, <er>Save</er>, <er>Salvo</er> an
exception.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Free from harm, injury, or risk;
untouched or unthreatened by danger or injury; unharmed; unhurt; secure;
whole; <as>as, <ex>safe</ex> from disease; <ex>safe</ex> from storms;
<ex>safe</ex> from foes</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧And ye dwelled
<xex>safe</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>1 Sam. xii. 11.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They escaped all <qex>safe</qex> to land.</q> <rj><qau>Acts xxvii.
44.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Established in a <qex>safe</qex>, unenvied throne.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Conferring safety; securing from harm; not exposing
to danger; confining securely; to be relied upon; not dangerous; <as>as,
a <ex>safe</ex> harbor; a <ex>safe</ex> bridge, etc.</as></def>
⟦ldquo⟧The man of <xex>safe</xex> discretion.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The King of heaven hath doomed⟦br⟧
This place our dungeon, not our <qex>safe</qex> retreat.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1267 pr=PCP --></p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Incapable of doing harm; no longer dangerous; in
secure care or custody; <as>as, the prisoner is
<ex>safe</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But Banquo's <qex>safe</qex>?⟦br⟧
Ay, my good lord, <qex>safe</qex> in a ditch he bides.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Safe hit</b></col> <fld>(Baseball)</fld>, <cd>a hit which
enables the batter to get to first base even if no error is made by the
other side.</cd> <-- <col><b>safe house</b></col>, <cd>a residence where
a person in hiding from the authorities or other persons may stay
without being discovered.</cd> --></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Secure; unendangered; sure.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Safe</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Safe
<hw>Safe</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A place for keeping
things in safety.</def> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>A strong and fireproof receptacle (as a movable chest of steel,
etc., or a closet or vault of brickwork) for containing money, valuable
papers, or the like.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A ventilated or
refrigerated chest or closet for securing provisions from noxious
animals or insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Safe</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Safe
<hw>Safe</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To render safe; to make
right.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Safe-conduct</ent>⟦br⟧
